trend_summary: Earliest imagery shows a leafy suburb flanking a freeway. Subsequent years bring highway widening, a re-engineered interchange and new commercial sheds near the ramps. Vacant residential plots are gradually infilled, slightly reducing tree cover. Overall form stays detached-house suburbia with modest growth, not wholesale transformation.
notable_changes: Cloverleaf interchange on the east enlarged, adding extra lanes and ramps
Light-industrial/commercial buildings constructed south of the interchange
Vacant residential lots built out with new detached houses and cul-de-sacs
Edge woodlands thinned and some trees removed for road and lot expansion
Parking area footprint increases around public or institutional blocks
